3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Aevo calculates APT/USDT funding rates every hour using mark-to-index price divergence and interest rate components. The platform's off-chain order book aggregates pricing data while maintaining on-chain settlement integrity through its dedicated rollup. Funding payments flow between long and short positions based on the premium/discount to spot APT prices. Aevo's infrastructure enables rapid funding calculations without Ethereum mainnet congestion affecting settlement timing."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","APT","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"APT represents a major L1 blockchain with significant institutional backing, making it attractive for funding rate strategies due to consistent trading volume. The token's correlation with broader crypto markets while maintaining independent price action creates predictable funding patterns. Aevo's pre-launch market capabilities often provide early APT derivative exposure, potentially generating higher funding premiums during momentum periods."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"APT Funding Rate Historical Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"APT funding rates on Aevo typically range from -0.05% to 0.15% during normal market conditions, with spikes reaching 0.3%+ during major Aptos ecosystem announcements. The token shows distinct funding cycles aligned with DeFi activity on the Aptos network and developer grant releases. Historical data indicates negative funding rates occur roughly 30% of the time, often coinciding with broader market downturns or Move ecosystem FUD. Weekend trading sessions frequently exhibit lower absolute funding rates due to reduced institutional activity. Major Aptos partnership announcements or ecosystem milestones typically drive 24-48 hour periods of elevated positive funding."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities on Aevo"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Aevo's rollup architecture enables faster arbitrage execution compared to mainnet-based competitors, particularly beneficial for APT cross-exchange strategies. The platform's options integration creates unique delta-neutral opportunities combining APT perps with call/put spreads. Funding rate premiums often exceed 0.2% during APT ecosystem events, making short-term arbitrage profitable after factoring Aevo's competitive fee structure. Pre-launch APT derivatives sometimes trade at significant premiums to eventual spot prices, creating structured arbitrage setups. The DEX nature means no KYC friction for large arbitrage positions, enabling institutional-scale strategies."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Mitigation"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Aevo's rollup centralization presents unique counterparty risks not found in traditional CEX arbitrage, requiring careful position sizing and exit planning. APT's moderate liquidity means large funding arbitrage positions can impact mark prices, reducing effective returns. The platform's smaller liquidity pools compared to major CEXs can create slippage issues during volatile periods or large position adjustments. Smart contract risks exist despite Aevo's audited infrastructure, particularly around the bridge mechanisms connecting the rollup to mainnet. Cross-exchange arbitrage requires careful timing due to APT's occasional correlation breaks with major tokens like ETH and SOL."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What makes APT funding rates different on Aevo compared to centralized exchanges?","answer":"Aevo's DEX nature and smaller liquidity pools often result in higher funding rate volatility for APT compared to major CEXs. The platform's options integration also creates unique supply/demand dynamics affecting perpetual funding. Additionally, Aevo's rollup infrastructure enables more frequent rate updates without gas cost constraints."},{"question":"How does Aevo's hourly funding frequency affect APT arbitrage strategies?","answer":"The 1-hour funding intervals provide more frequent profit realization compared to 8-hour standard intervals on most exchanges. This enables shorter-term arbitrage strategies but requires more active position management. Higher frequency also means funding rates can change direction more rapidly during volatile APT price movements."},{"question":"What are the liquidity considerations for large APT funding arbitrage positions on Aevo?","answer":"APT liquidity on Aevo is moderate, meaning positions above $50K may start impacting market prices and reducing arbitrage efficiency. The platform's institutional user base helps with larger trades, but position sizing should account for potential slippage. Exit liquidity can become constrained during high volatility periods."},{"question":"How do Aevo's bridge mechanics affect APT arbitrage timing?","answer":"Deposits and withdrawals between Aevo's rollup and mainnet can take 10-30 minutes depending on network congestion. This affects the speed of cross-exchange arbitrage setups requiring frequent capital movement. Fast arbitrage strategies should maintain adequate collateral on multiple platforms to avoid bridge delays."}]}]
